    "narrative": "The slate for April 10 features a balanced lineup with significant upside, led by **Daulton Varsho** (72.16) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.61). **Daulton Varsho** earns the top spot today; while he faces a decent arm in Simeon Woods Richardson, his elite hold on base paths creates a high-leverage scenario for our stolen base-starved roster. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a staple in the cleanup-adjacent spot, providing a massive floor against Bryce Elder. **Jonathan Aranda** and **Matt Chapman** also profile as high-end starts (70.47 and 70.11, respectively). **Jonathan Aranda** benefits immensely from a soft matchup against Luis Gil, whose 5.74 xERA is the most exploitable on the board, while **Matt Chapman** enjoys a favorable park factor and the added benefit of Shane Baz\u2019s slow delivery, which keeps our stolen base potential in play despite the catcher\u2019s defensive profile.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Brendan Donovan** (59.16), who fell just shy of our 60-point \"Strong\" threshold. While his 14% platoon edge against Tatsuya Imai made him an attractive high-volume option, the optimizer favored the higher park-adjusted floors provided by **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Jung Hoo Lee**. We are also keeping a close watch on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, particularly **Will Smith** and **Cal Raleigh**; should they shift lower in their respective batting orders, their scores will regress, potentially necessitating a move to the bench to preserve our limited game caps. \n\nOverall, the lineup is optimized to maximize plate appearances in hitter-friendly environments. With **Tyler Freeman** and **Taylor Ward** benefiting from significant park upgrades, we are well-positioned to capitalize on offensive volatility today. We have left **Gavin Sheets**, **Gleyber Torres**, and **Yainer Diaz** on the pine to mitigate the risk of sub-60 performances, ensuring that every slot in the lineup is firing at a \"Strong\" efficiency level or better. We remain aggressive in seeking stolen bases, banking on the mobility of **Daulton Varsho**, **Matt Chapman**, and **Tyler Freeman** to navigate the defensive limitations of their respective opponents.",
